# Styling Rules
- Tailwind CSS only — no inline styles, no CSS-in-JS
- Use `cn()` utility (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional class names
- Responsive design is mobile-first: start with base, add `md:` / `lg:` breakpoints
- Use CSS variables for theme tokens defined in `globals.css`
- Never hardcode colors — use Tailwind's design tokens